CatDescriptText: Mr. Ralph Terry, 1848 Cliff Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 16, 1958, pg. 3 with question: "Do you think that Negroes are giving sufficient financial help to the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People?" answer reads: "No, and the reason why is that the leaders are not getting down and pushing fast enough. Anything that you want you have to push for it."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Ralph Terry, wearing button down collared shirt, untucked with rolled up sleeves, and cap, standing with left hand in pocket against light colored wall, glass double doors and store window displaying women's dresses on right, buildings and pedestrians on left
